# Patch: Occurrences.kerml end-keyword cross-feature participant
#
# Adds the `end` keyword to the `surroundedSpace` and `surroundingSpace`
# cross-feature participants in
# `Occurrences::Occurrence::SurroundedSpacePerformances` so that this
# LSP's `checkFeatureCrossingSpecialization` validator does not fire
# falsely against an otherwise spec-conformant declaration. Upstream
# omits the keyword because the pilot infers end-ness from `crosses`
# semantics; this LSP does not yet.
#
# Source: bundled-fork divergence from upstream (sysml-2ls 2026-03
# upgrade, Phase 1b). Identified as the only load-bearing fork patch
# by P1a's empirical reclassification harness
# (`scripts/reclassify-patches.ts`); see
# `docs/maintenance/upgrades/2026-03/02-library-builtins-fork-patches.md`.
#
# Retirement criterion: when `checkFeatureCrossingSpecialization` no
# longer reports a diagnostic for the un-patched upstream form (i.e.
# the validator correctly accepts end-inference through `crosses`
# semantics for cross-feature participants).
#
--- a/sysml.library/Kernel Libraries/Kernel Semantic Library/Occurrences.kerml
+++ b/sysml.library/Kernel Libraries/Kernel Semantic Library/Occurrences.kerml
@@ -601,8 +601,8 @@
 			 * Occurrences that have inner spaces that completely include this occurrence.
 			 */

-			feature surroundedSpace: Occurrence [1] subsets that;
-			feature surroundingSpace: Occurrence [1] subsets self;
+			end feature surroundedSpace: Occurrence [1] subsets that;
+			end feature surroundingSpace: Occurrence [1] subsets self;

 			connector :InsideOf
 				from [0..1] smallerOccurrence references surroundedSpace
